<blockquote>
<p>these segments of sentences imply Dr. Mann is dealing with a corpse rather than a still-living person. Unless he intends to saw the boy apart to begin his procedure, this is unlikely.</p>
</blockquote>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Potential&nbsp;squick</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>There are some surgical procedures used to remove brain tumors that require that the skull be sawed open, sometimes when the patient is still conscious (to ensure that they can respond to &quot;move your left hand&quot; questions so the surgeon is able to ensure that they don't damage anything).</p>
<p>Lots of pain meds are in effect at that time. I had to watch a video involving a brain surgery in bio class. I put my head down when the buzzing started.</p>
</div>
